<h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--mobile-top-margin  " id="details-title">Details</h2>


<div aria-labelledby="details-title">
  
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>It will still be a criminal offence to ship radioactive waste and spent fuel without valid authorisation and documentation.</p>

<p>If the UK leaves the EU without a deal on 12 April 2019, operators may need to get new authorisations to ship radioactive waste or spent fuel.</p>

<p>See the related guides on:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/prepare-to-import-relevant-nuclear-materials-from-the-eu-after-brexit-licensing-requirements/importing-relevant-nuclear-materials-from-the-eu-if-theres-no-brexit-deal-licensing-requirements">importing nuclear materials</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/exporting-nuclear-related-items-after-the-uk-leaves-the-eu/exporting-nuclear-related-items-after-the-uk-leaves-the-eu">exporting nuclear materials</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/shipping-radioactive-sources-between-the-uk-and-eu-after-brexit/shipping-radioactive-sources-between-the-uk-and-eu-after-a-no-deal-brexit">shipping radioactive sources</a></li>
</ul>

</div>
